{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Second review BLOCK remediation:\n- Replaced raw STATUS-history scanning with a reducer-maintained execution_mode projection that survives SNAPSHOT compaction; phase story file impact now includes reducer implementation and tests.\n- Defined priority-floor syntax as numeric [0.0,1.0], with compatibility >=0.80.\n- Clarified gate composition: pin enforcement never activates close by itself; close blocks on pins only when both close-review and pin-enforcement flags are enabled.\n- Kept 0.80 non-configurable, but specified its numeric forward-evolution behavior so threshold changes require re-review, not a manifest migration.\n- Split epic and phase acceptance criteria into independently observable outcomes.\n- Named shared internal contracts for relation snapshots, validity profiles, phase compatibility ownership, and derived health consumers to prevent sibling implementations from diverging.\nRerunning the epic review; no child review starts until it signs."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784519761129454001,"uuid":"a954f53e-96a4-40c4-abcc-b08cafe98aec"}